 Career History



Chief Compliance Officer & Chief Financial Officer

                                    2013 - Prior                


Geller Family Office Services LLC


                  Geller Family Office Services' asset allocation recommendations are based on a customized, comprehensive financial plan that is based on each client's individual objectives, time horizons, risk tolerance, tax considerations, and liquidity needs. They stress-test potential strategic allocations through the imposition of historical scenarios, during which the risks of loss in securities and the potential for all asset classes to perform similarly are observed. This process also establishes the degree to which portions of the portfolio can have limited liquidity. Portfolio construction typically involves establishing a risk-appropriate allocation among cash, fixed income, global equities and alternatives, such as hedge funds where appropriate. Global equity allocations are usually indexed to varying degrees in a \"\"core and satellite\"\" structure. The satellite managers typically have concentrated holdings and may exhibit meaningful divergence from their benchmarks. In addition, such a plan can support selective use of alternative investments, appropriately sized to meet individual liquidity needs. Geller Family Office may allocate a client’s assets among several third party investment managers, which may include mutual funds, separate account managers, hedge funds, private equity and other investments and ETFs. Client portfolio holdings may also include individual equities and fixed income, option contracts, warrants, certificates of deposit and commercial paper. Portfolio weighting among third party investment managers and other investments is determined by each client's asset allocation.                





